### VARAC MODULE INSTRUCTIONS ###

VarAC is a real-time keyboard-to-keyboard chat application for the VARA
digital mode. This module provides VarAC integration for arcOS with full
persistence and DigiRig support.

PREREQUISITES:
- VARA must be enabled in arcOS station-setup
- VARA module must have run successfully at least once
- DigiRig connected and configured

INSTALLATION:

1) Move the VARAC directory into the USER Module directory.
   /arcHIVE/QRV/<YOURCALL>/arcos-linux-modules/USER/

2) Move the included 40_VARAC.sh script into the USER Module directory.
   - Up one level from the VARAC directory

3) Reboot or re-run Station Setup.

FIRST RUN:
- VarAC will be extracted and configured automatically
- Your callsign will be set from station-info
- "Linux Compatible Mode" is enabled by default (required for Wine)
- Find VarAC in the Applications menu under HamRadio

USAGE:
- Launch VarAC from the Applications menu
- VARA HF modem will start automatically if not running
- All settings are saved when you close VarAC
- Settings persist across reboots

CONFIGURATION:
- PTT is handled by VARA modem (already configured for DigiRig)
- VARA connects on localhost:8300
- Frequency/chat preferences are stored on /arcHIVE

TROUBLESHOOTING:
- If you see black text boxes, ensure "Linux Compatible Mode" is ON
  (Settings -> General -> Linux Compatible Mode)
- If VARA modem doesn't start, launch it manually first
- Check logs at: VARAC/VARAC.log

Notes:
- The module will be active on the next reboot or re-run of Station Setup.
- You may re-number it if necessary for your ordering preferences.
- To deactivate the module, place the 40_VARAC.sh script back inside
  the VARAC directory and reboot.
- In multi-user installations, VARAC will remain configured for a
  previous user if the next user does not also use this module.
